<br>
One of the major complaints about the new interface from the magician community was that our HP bar was split by our pet health bar.  I rectified this <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
No pet up:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/ui/1.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Pet at full health:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/ui/2.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
Mouse over info:<br>
<!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/ui/3.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--><br>
<br>
If you're a test player and want to install this change (or you just want to play around with the /loadskin command <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END-->):<br>
<br>
1) Go to C:\Program Files\EverQuest\uifiles and copy and rename your &quot;default&quot; directory (&quot;petbar&quot; for this example)<br>
<br>
2) Right click <!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/ui/EQUI_PlayerWindow.xml">here</a><!--EZCODE LINK END-->, choose Save As, and save it in your C:\Program Files\EverQuest\uifiles\petbar directory.<br>
<br>
3) Type &quot;/loadskin petbar&quot; (without the quotes) in EQ to make the change <!--EZCODE IMAGE START--><img src="http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif"><!--EZCODE IMAGE END--> <p><img src="http://www.danos.pwp.blueyonder.co.uk/deadgnome.gif" width="535" height="245"></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uedano.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Edano</A> at: 6/26/02 6:48:12 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=rhasinfirestorm>Rhasin Firestorm</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 895<br> <font color=#333333>(6/26/02 6:30:14 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerfrm45.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: EverQuest mod:  Seperate pet health bar</span><hr size=1> Simple statement here, but I don't think I could say it well enough.<br>
